# Executive Risk Summary

## Purpose

This report summarizes key findings from the ISO 27001:2022 risk assessment.

## Key Findings

- 12 risks identified
- 4 High Risks
- 5 Medium Risks
- 3 Low Risks

## Major Risk Areas

- Phishing
- Vendor compromise
- Weak password practices
- Unauthorized cloud access

## Recommended Actions

- Implement MFA
- Security awareness training
- Vendor security reviews
- Quarterly access reviews

## Conclusion

The organization should prioritize remediation of high-risk findings and continuously monitor information security controls.
